                "name": "Alex Johnston",
                "href": "/profile/Alex-Johnston-39"
            },
            "answer_text": "Let me answer that question with another question: What would you rather do: a.) create new music which doesn\u2019t sound like anything else but which nobody likes, or b.) create music which resembles existing music but which people can connect with, and which moves them enough that they love it? The point, in case I haven\u2019t made it sufficiently clear, is not to sacrifice everything that makes music powerful, moving and effective for the sake of mere \u2018newness\u2019. The point is to connect with people using music. In the meantime, I guarantee you that no matter what music anyone makes, someone somewhere has already made music that resembles it, even if you\u2019ve never heard it. Get over it. Only connect. ",
